    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A script developed by the early 7th century from the later Roman cursive and first known from charters issued by the Merovingian kings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000083235/Thompson, Introduction to Greek and Latin Palaeography (1912)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000006661/Brown, Guide to Western Historical Scripts (1990)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een schrift ontwikkeld tegen het begin van de 7e eeuw vanuit het oudere Romeins cursief, dat als eerste werd gevonden in handvesten verspreid door de Merovingische koningen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>西元七世紀早期由晚期羅馬草寫體所發展而來的書體，由法國墨洛溫王朝的國王首次使用於憲章中。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
